records.addlTxt:
Defendant Andrew J Arnold in court with attorney Nicole Buttery for attorney Tedia K. Gamino.  Mary Caitlin Brejcha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant entered a plea of no contest to count 3. Court conducted plea colloquy with defendant.
Court found defendant guilty of count 3. Count 2 dismissed and read-in and Count 4 dismissed by operation of law. 

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

225 DAYS STRAIGHT TIME (CREDIT - 3 days);

*D/L REVOCATION: 30 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 30 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  20 MONTHS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment;
*No Contact with codefendant;
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel during the period of probation.
*Do not drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid license.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done (no surcharges).

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forwarded to City of Waukesha Police Department);

FINE:  $1744.00 to be paid as a condition of probation includes $200.00 DNA surcharge;

CONDITION TIME:  75 DAYS NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions. After first 45 days served, balance to be served on the Day Report Program. Defendant remanded to the Sheriff's department to commence sentence. 

$500.00 cash bail to be refunded to poster.
